net.proteusframework.users.model

Class AllPermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.users.model.AcegiPermission
      • net.proteusframework.users.model.AllPermission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Entity<Long>

    @Entity
public class AllPermission
extends AcegiPermission
    Permission that implies all other permissions. This permission should not be directly checked. Assignment of this permission to a role or principal grants the role or principal *all* other AcegiPermissions. This is intended for assignment to a small number of system level administrators.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • implies

        public boolean implies(AcegiPermission permission)
        Description copied from class: AcegiPermission
        Checks if the specified permission's actions are "implied by" this object's actions.

        The implies method is used by the PermissionCheckProvider to determine whether or not a requested permission is implied by another permission.

        Overrides:
        implies in class AcegiPermission
        Parameters:
        permission - the permission to check against.
        Returns:
        true if the specified permission is implied by this object, false if not.
